main event: Two objects identified as red flashing circles were sighted in Teaticket, Massachusetts on 27 April 1966.
interesting points: The observer described the objects as the size of two apples,The sighting lasted for approximately 10 minutes,Upon disappearance, two red lights resembling rocket thrust appeared above the horizon,The objects made a level flight until ignition of the thrust,The probable cause was determined to be an F-106 aircraft's afterburner and navigation lights.
witness description: students and staff in Teaticket, Massachusetts
